Enrichment Analysis

GO Enrichment Analysis

ego <- enrichGO(gene = genes.target, universe = genes.bg, OrgDb = org.Hs.eg.db, keyType = "SYMBOL", ont = "ALL",
    pAdjustMethod = "BH", minGSSize = 2, maxGSSize = 500, pvalueCutoff = 0.03, qvalueCutoff = 0.05)
# head(ego, 20)
saveRDS(object = ego, file = "~/bio/code/mpip/dex-stim-human-array/output/data/integrative/matrixEQTL/05_me-qtl_enrichment/clusterProfile_rslt/delta_meqtl_cpgs_enrichGO_rslt.rds")
bar.plt <- 
  mutate(ego, p.adj = -log(p.adjust, base=10)) %>%
      barplot(x = "p.adj",
              font.size = 8,
                   # split = "ONTOLOGY",
                   showCategory = 30,
              ) + 
      # geom_text(
      #   aes(label = Count),
      #   color = "black",
      #   hjust = -0.1,
      #   size = 3,
      #   position = position_identity()) +
      theme(
        panel.background = element_blank(),
        panel.border = element_blank(),
        plot.title = element_text(size = 8),
        axis.title = element_text(size = 8),
        legend.position = "bottom",
        axis.title.y = element_blank(),
        strip.text.x = element_text(size = 8, face = "bold"),
    )

bar.plt

GO analysis. The distributions of the enriched GO terms 

dot.plt <- 
      dotplot(ego, 
              x = "GeneRatio",
                   split = "ONTOLOGY",
                   showCategory = 30,
                   font.size = 8,
              orderBy = "x") + 
      geom_text(
        aes(label = Count),
        color = "black",
        hjust = -0.2,
        size = 3,
        position = position_identity()) +
      theme(
        panel.background = element_blank(),
        # strip.background = element_blank()
        panel.border = element_blank(),
        plot.title = element_text(size = 10),
        axis.title = element_text(size = 8),
        legend.position = "bottom",
        # panel.grid.minor = element_blank(),
        # panel.grid = element_blank(),
        # axis.text.x = element_blank(),
        # axis.ticks = element_blank(),
        axis.title.y = element_blank(),
        strip.text.x = element_text(size = 8, face = "bold"),
    )

KEGG pathway enrichment analysis

ekegg <- enrichKEGG(gene = target.ids$ENTREZID, universe = bg.ids$ENTREZID, organism = "hsa", keyType = "kegg",
    pAdjustMethod = "BH", minGSSize = 2, maxGSSize = 500, pvalueCutoff = 0.5)

saveRDS(object = ekegg, file = "~/bio/code/mpip/dex-stim-human-array/output/data/integrative/matrixEQTL/05_me-qtl_enrichment/clusterProfile_rslt/delta_meqtl_cpgs_enrichKEGG_rslt.rds")
dot.plt <- 
      dotplot(ekegg, 
              x = "GeneRatio",
                   showCategory = 30,
                   font.size = 8,
              orderBy = "x") + 
      geom_text(
        aes(label = Count),
        color = "black",
        hjust = -0.2,
        size = 3,
        position = position_identity()) +
      theme(
        panel.background = element_blank(),
        # strip.background = element_blank()
        panel.border = element_blank(),
        plot.title = element_text(size = 8),
        axis.title = element_text(size = 8),
        legend.position = "right",
        # panel.grid.minor = element_blank(),
        # panel.grid = element_blank(),
        # axis.text.x = element_blank(),
        # axis.ticks = element_blank(),
        axis.title.y = element_blank(),
        strip.text.x = element_text(size = 8, face = "bold"),
    )

Disease enrichment analysis

library(DOSE)
edo <- enrichDO(gene = target.ids$ENTREZID, universe = bg.ids$ENTREZID, ont = "DO", pvalueCutoff = 1,
    pAdjustMethod = "BH", minGSSize = 2, maxGSSize = 500, qvalueCutoff = 1, readable = FALSE)

saveRDS(object = edo, file = "~/bio/code/mpip/dex-stim-human-array/output/data/integrative/matrixEQTL/05_me-qtl_enrichment/clusterProfile_rslt/delta_meqtl_cpgs_enrichDO_rslt.rds")
dot.plt <- 
      dotplot(edo, 
              x = "GeneRatio",
                   showCategory = 30,
                   font.size = 8,
              orderBy = "x") + 
      geom_text(
        aes(label = Count),
        color = "black",
        hjust = -0.2,
        size = 3,
        position = position_identity()) +
      theme(
        panel.background = element_blank(),
        # strip.background = element_blank()
        panel.border = element_blank(),
        plot.title = element_text(size = 8),
        axis.title = element_text(size = 8),
        legend.position = "right",
        # panel.grid.minor = element_blank(),
        # panel.grid = element_blank(),
        # axis.text.x = element_blank(),
        # axis.ticks = element_blank(),
        axis.title.y = element_blank(),
        strip.text.x = element_text(size = 8, face = "bold"),
    )
